#eNCA Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - The Environmental Affairs Department is sending 12 of the fastest land animals to India. It is part of a cooperation agreement between the two countries to reintroduce the species. READ: India welcomes back cheetahs, 70 years after local extinction In 2022, India received eight cheetahs from Namibia which were released at the Kuno National Park. South Africa plans to send a similar number annually over the next 8 to 10 years to help reestablish a viable population.